==English==

===Pronunciation===
*: {{rhymes|eɪviə}}

===Etymology===
[[Late Latin]], alteration of {{term|Scadinavia}}, from {{etyl|gem}} *''Skadinaujo'' 'Scadia island' (compare {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term|Scedenig|lang=ang}}, {{etyl|non|-}} {{term|Skaney|lang=non}} 'southern tip of Sweden'), from *-''aujo'' 'island' (compare {{etyl|ang|-}} ''ī(e)g'' 'island', {{etyl|non|-}} {{term|ey}} 'island').

===Proper noun===
[[Image:Scandinavia location map definitions.PNG|thumb|right|''Red'': The three monarchies that compose Scandinavia according to the strictest definition<br /><br />''Orange'': The possible extended usage<br /><br />''Yellow'': The maximal extended usage that takes Scandinavia as synonymous to the [[Nordic countries]]]]
